{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595229","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595229"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:01:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:01:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15340"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15340"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.2,0.1,0.07,0.6,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8031"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66474"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8031","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8031"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15340"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51927"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19509"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19512"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66474","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66474"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECirrhosis represents the final common pathway of chronic liver injury, characterised by fibrosis and nodular regeneration.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common complication of cirrhosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Coagulopathy","Hepatorenal syndrome","Hepatopulmonary syndrome","Ascites","Spontaneous bacterial peritonitis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAscites\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common complication of cirrhosis, occurring in about 50% of patients within 10 years of diagnosis. It develops due to portal hypertension and reduced plasma oncotic pressure from decreased albumin synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoagulopathy\u003C/strong\u003E is also common but occurs later in the disease process due to decreased synthesis of clotting factors. \u003Cstrong\u003EHepatorenal syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a serious but less common complication characterised by progressive renal failure. \u003Cstrong\u003EHepatopulmonary syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a relatively rare complication involving intrapulmonary vascular dilatations. \u003Cstrong\u003ESpontaneous bacterial peritonitis\u003C/strong\u003E is a serious infection that can complicate ascites but occurs less frequently.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Portal hypertension leads to ascites as the most common complication of cirrhosis.","Ascites develops in approximately 50% of patients with compensated cirrhosis within 10 years of diagnosis.","The development of ascites marks the transition from compensated to decompensated cirrhosis."],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51927"}},"question":{"d